description:
This is the official video guide 📝 on how to use Samsung Smart Switch to transfer data to your new Galaxy smartphone. Move contacts, photos, and more in no time! Smart Switch makes switching to Galaxy smartphone safe and easy. Learn more: http://smsng.co/Smart-Switch_yt

00:00 Intro 
00:15 Moving data from iOS using a cable
01:44 Moving data from iOS wirelessly
03:27 Moving data from Android wirelessly

Follow these simple steps to transfer your data with Smart Switch:
Step 1: Swipe up on your Home screen to open the Smart Switch app.
Step 2: Tap ‘Receive on this phone’ and choose your old device type. 
Step 3: Connect both devices with a cable or wirelessly by scanning the QR code.
Step 4: Select the data you want to move.
Step 5: Wait for Smart Switch to complete the transfer.

Why use Samsung Smart Switch?
1. Data transfer across devices and OS: Move important data to a new Galaxy, whether you’re switching from iOS or Android.
